+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TUNhFwtiesM5ampg27WpEm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Phase 2: Named Queues\n     2→\n     3→Extend the system to support multiple independent queues, each identified by a name.\n     4→\n     5→## Requirements\n     6→\n     7→- Tasks are added to a specific named queue. If no name is given, a default queue is used.\n     8→- Each named queue operates independently -- adding to one does not affect another.\n     9→- Retrieving a task pulls from the specified queue only.\n    10→- Creating a queue happens implicitly when a task is first added to it.\n    11→- There should be a way to list all queue names that exist.\n    12→- Asking for a task from a non-existent or empty queue returns `null`.\n    13→- The API should remain backward-compatible with Phase 1 (omitting the queue name uses the default).\n    14→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8d05ce79-98b1-4890-9460-df7d22557abf","uuid":"10f804e2-9368-4fad-8c15-198fecfb5f43","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/phases/phase-02.md","content":"# Phase 2: Named Queues\n\nExtend the system to support multiple independent queues, each identified by a name.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Tasks are added to a specific named queue. If no name is given, a default queue is used.\n- Each named queue operates independently -- adding to one does not affect another.\n- Retrieving a task pulls from the specified queue only.\n- Creating a queue happens implicitly when a task is first added to it.\n- There should be a way to list all queue names that exist.\n- Asking for a task from a non-existent or empty queue returns `null`.\n- The API should remain backward-compatible with Phase 1 (omitting the queue name uses the default).\n","numLines":14,"startLine":1,"totalLines":14}}}
