+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01CmLZr84ipFg6Um2XVrtLpb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"My architectural design:\n\n**File structure:**\n- `src/types.ts` - All interfaces and type definitions\n- `src/task.ts` - Task class\n- `src/queue.ts` - Individual queue (named queue with priority, delay, concurrency, DLQ, middleware)\n- `src/cron.ts` - Cron parser for recurring tasks\n- `src/task-queue.ts` - Main TaskQueue class orchestrating everything\n- `src/index.ts` - Re-exports\n\n**Key design decisions:**\n1. `TaskQueue` is the main facade class that manages named queues internally\n2. Each named queue (`Queue`) holds its own sorted task list, DLQ, middleware stack, concurrency settings\n3. Tasks are stored in a Map by ID for O(1) lookup, and queues maintain sorted arrays for retrieval\n4. Priority sorting: lower number = higher priority, then by creation order\n5. Delayed tasks: checked at retrieval time via `availableAt` timestamp\n6. Dependencies: global task registry in TaskQueue, circular detection via DFS\n7. Progress: event emitter pattern with callbacks\n8. Recurring: schedules stored centrally, `tick()` checks against current time\n9. Middleware: chain of `(task, next) => void` functions\n10. Shutdown: promise-based with timeout\n\nLet me use Gemini to help implement the types file first, then the main implementation."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":580,"cache_read_input_tokens":27400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":580},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8d05ce79-98b1-4890-9460-df7d22557abf","uuid":"f189df09-341e-40de-8af2-283a6017fe13"}
